PROCEDURE
---------
- assemble the raspberry pi into it's case

- connect 
  - wireless keyboard & mouse
  - display
  - wireless network
  - flash card
  - power

- raspi-config will autostart, select
  1 expand filesystem
  3 enable boot to desktop
  4 tz
  Finish

- next it reboots and loads desktop, configure
  - terminal monospace 14
  - wifi : scan, select network, enter key, connect

- setup pi login
  - update router to make ip addr static, and add ip addr to development system's /etc/hosts
  - send over .ssh dir, and verify login without password
  - update .profile
      PATH=".:$PATH"
  - update .bashrc
      alias ls='ls -l'
  - mkdir proj_cam bin
  - copy files to bin dir

- setup files in /etc
  - rc.local: add the following
      # Start wc_server
      if [ -x /home/pi/proj_cam/wc_server ]
      then
        su pi -c "cd /home/pi/proj_cam; ./wc_server </dev/null >/dev/null 2>&1 &"
      fi

- setup additional development software
  - sudo apt-get install libjpeg8-dev
  - sudo apt-get install libreadline6-dev

- build and install wc_server 
  - bin/install_raspberry_pi

- apply usb patch
  - add the folloing to /boot/cmdline.txt, and reboot
      dwc_otg.fiq_fsm_enable=0
  - see https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux/issues/618 for information
  - this seems to fix a webcam failure that occurs when closing and reopening the /dev/video0

- disconnect wireless keyboard and mouse and connect camera, and reboot


NOTES
-----

login pi, password raspberry

raspi-config can be rerun later

downloading new flash image and copy on to micro sd card
- get Raspbian OS image from raspberrypi.org/downloads
- insert SD Card into computer
- umount all filesystems mounted on from the SD card, for example
    umount /dev/sdb5
    umount /dev/sdb6
- dd bs=4M if=xxx.img of=/dev/sdb
- monitor progress of dd by sending it SIGUSR1
    pkill -USR1 -n -x dd
- when done 'sync' and remove SD card

to get list of available packages
  apt-cache search <keyword>
